-- REJECT (F1): a class-mix (`x & 1 == 0`, bitwise mixed with comparison) in a
-- function NOT reachable from main. C rejects class-mix syntactically for ALL
-- functions, so native must too -- reachability-independent, with a clean ERR 442
-- (not silently emit an ELF, not crash). main never calls dead(); the mix is in
-- the dead function only.
func main():
    return 7
end
func dead(x):
    return x & 1 == 0
end
